## What we did

We used the Engage California platform to connect with over 1,600 state employees. We gathered more than 1,900 ideas to improve government operations.

----
id: why_we_did_it
title: Why we did it
----

## Why we did it

To build a better government, we need to engage directly with those who know it best: state employees. They are the experts on how the government works, how it doesn't, and how it should.

----
id: what_we_heard
----

## What we heard

California state employees are deeply committed to public service. They were grateful for the chance to share their knowledge. They took the engagement seriously and showed they care about their work and the communities they support.

**The main problem areas are clear. People cited hiring practices, employee training, and complex purchasing processes most often.**

**But the greatest value this engagement offers is the thoughtful solutions shared.**

The collective submissions reveal a clear vision. One where efficiency drives both growth and inclusivity.

People underscored the importance of organizational culture. They suggested ways to boost employee morale. They called out ways to improve customer service. And they outlined paths to save time by building on lessons learned.

